    <h2>The science of losing weight</h2>
    <div class="media-body">
        <a href="http://www.balancewellness.co.uk/zNEWsite_idea/fooditems.php"><img class="img-responsive pull-right hidden-sx" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="Image courtesy of David Lorenzana via Wikimedia Commons" src="http://www.balancewellness.co.uk/zNEWsite_idea/images/foods-cat_256px.png" alt="Food groups / types" /></a>
        <p>Losing weight by eating well and exercising can sometimes be hit and miss and not be an exact science. There are times you think you&rsquo;ve done everything right only to find you are not losing as much weight as you&rsquo;d hoped. Maintain your weight may be harder still, especially given the very many temptations that comes along moment by moment.</p>
	    <p class="hidden-sx">Regardless, it can be done! Yes, you can lose those extra kilograms or pounds, and maintain your weight at a healthy level! All it takes is a daily habit of good eating and exercise practices. There are several resources on this website to help you in your quests. Links to other resources have also been suggested. Above all, remember it can be done &hellip; and good luck!</p>
	    <p>Many of the resources on this website are free and some require registration. Either way, it is a great idea to register any so you can have access to all the resources and support we have to offer; all based on reliable sources and from personal experiences. So why don&rsquo;t you go ahead and register NOW!</p>
